<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1896,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,381,1896,1923]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Updated diagnosis.</emphasis>
In addition to the diagnosis presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bustamante, A. A. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S." box="[868,1240,1896,1923]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" pagination="301 - 347" refId="ref11153" refString="Bustamante, A. A. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S. (2017) Systematics of Thiodinini (Araneae: Salticidae: Salticinae), with description of a new genus and twelve new species. Zootaxa, 4362 (3), 301 - 347. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4362.3.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Bustamante &amp; Ruiz (2017: 310)</bibRefCitation>
, we included the following comparisons due the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz, 2020" authorityName="Bustamante &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2020" box="[672,904,1932,1958]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cyllodania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marietae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[672,904,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Cyllodania marietae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[911,1002,1933,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[911,1002,1933,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see below): 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[1156,1316,1932,1958]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atomosphyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1156,1316,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Atomosphyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[151,275,1968,1994]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cyllodania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,275,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Cyllodania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a mastidion proximally on the male chelicera (common in amycoids), but differs by not having a longitudinal band of white scales on the abdominal dorsum and by having a slender femur I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
